Bunzl buys U . S . grocery supply business . British paper and plastics group Bunzl Plc said on Friday that it has agreed to buy the grocery supply systems division along with other related grocery supply business from Unisource Worldwide Inc of the U . S . for about 88 million dollars . The business supplies disposable products to supermarkets and other grocery outlets throughout the U . S . and has annual sales in excess of 300 million dollars . - - London Newsroom + 44 171 542 4019 
